# Ollama Modelfile — Llama 3.2 3B (128K native context)
# num_ctx set to 131072 per Meta docs; the model supports 128K natively, not the 256k variant name suggests
# Research: Official Meta documentation + community coding agent tuning
# Sources: https://www.llama.com/docs/model-cards-and-prompt-formats/llama3_2/
# NOTE: Has min_p and repeat_penalty already. temp=0.6 is fine for a small model needing more creativity. Minor tweak to repeat_penalty from 1.1→1.15 for agent work where repetition is a known failure mode.
FROM llama3.2:3b

# --- Sampling: Meta coding settings (tuned for agent use) ---
# temperature=0.6 — Meta official; kept at this level since small models need more creativity to produce useful code
# top_p=0.9 — Meta official default
# top_k=16383 — Meta official (very wide sampling appropriate for small model vocabulary)
# min_p=0.05 — Meta recommended for filtering noise in small models
# repeat_penalty=1.15 — bumped from 1.1 per AkitaOnRails findings: agent work benefits from stronger repetition prevention; small models are more prone to token-level loops
PARAMETER temperature 0.6
PARAMETER top_p 0.9
PARAMETER top_k 16383
PARAMETER min_p 0.05
PARAMETER repeat_penalty 1.15

# --- Context & Generation ---
PARAMETER num_ctx 131072
PARAMETER num_predict 8192
